#HTML Boilerplate using Emmet

`Shift + !` is an **Emmet abbreviation** used in **Visual Studio Code** to quickly generate the basic HTML boilerplate structure.

**Emmet** is a toolkit that helps developers write HTML and CSS faster using short abbreviations. When you type `!` and press **Enter**, VS Code automatically creates the standard HTML template.

Example:

html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Document</title>
</head>
<body>

</body>
</html>

This provides a proper starting structure for any HTML webpage.

### Difference Between HTML Tags and HTML Elements

Many beginners think **HTML tags** and **HTML elements** are the same, but they are slightly different.

**HTML Tag**
A tag is the keyword inside angle brackets that defines the start or end of an element.

Example:

<p> OPEN TAG 
</p>CLOSE TAG 

**HTML Element**
An HTML element is the complete structure, including the opening tag, content, and closing tag.
AND IT CONTAIN ALL THE STRUCTURE FOR YOUR WORK 
Example:

